            <h2 id="2-speed-is-normal">2. Speed is the New Normal, Not Differentiation</h2>
            <p>According to <a href="https://cxtrends.zendesk.com/">Zendesk</a>, today, 74% of customers expect 24/7 service, and 88% expect faster responses than one year ago.</p>
            <p>Customers expect that the businesses they give their loyalty to will service them in the fastest possible time and every time they come knocking.</p>
            <p>Besides, there are always smarter competitors waiting to service your customers at the slightest delay from your end. Hence, speed has become the least competitive strategy out there. The rationale is simple: perform faster or get lost in the noise.</p>
            <p>This speed is achieved by automation.</p>
            <p>AI has completely redefined what "fast service" means. Customers want to be able to resolve issues as soon as they occur. Waiting two days for a routine request feels like a waste of time, archaic, and unserious.</p>
            <p>Verizon recently unveiled its AI-powered customer support using Google Cloud's Gemini models to provide smarter, personalized, and 24/7 support via app, text, and voice.</p>
            <p>This wasn't just a power move; it was the biggest differentiation customers needed to pick the brand they'd stay loyal to.</p>

            <h2 id="3-ai-first-orgs">3. The Companies That Are Winning Are The Ones Building AI-first organizations, Not Just AI tools.</h2>
            <p>AI has already brought about the biggest differentiation in the market as we speak. Yet, this differentiation isn't just about the use of AI tools.</p>
            <p>The competitive edge is no longer just about buying smarter software or implementing AI-compliant Addons. It is now about the smartness of the entire system.</p>
            <p>From product build to customer service support, payment and team standups, organizations that have embedded AI into the very fabrics of their operations, are winning.</p>
            <p>Organizations like JPMorgan Chase have successfully achieved this level of AI oneness, embedding AI in Finance, Fraud, and Verification.</p>
            <p>The COiN platform implements an AI to interpret legal documents and make review processes faster. There are also tailored chatbots for basic support and account assistance, and AI dashboards used in team planning and risk assessment meetings.</p>
            <p>Basically, at JPMorgan Chase, AI handles the day-to-day heavy lifting with precision.</p>

            <h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Business efficiency has shifted in leaps for good. Thanks to AI. Customers now have the liberty to choose, exercise more autonomy and feel more served in a business.</p>
            <p>This translates to higher patronage, more revenue and the ability to correctly iterate with real data extracted from customer behaviour on your site or page.</p>
            <p>This is not the future. It is the basic template today for business success.</p>

